[While these cases of persistent COVID only occurred in immunocompromised patients, according to the AMA "immunocompromised people account for at least 2.7% of U.S. adults -- about 7 million people. This includes those who have had organ transplants, stem cell transplants and cancer, as well as those with primary immunodeficiency and those treated with immunosuppressive medications." (https://www.ama-assn.org/delivering-care/public-health/what-tell-immunocompromised-patients-about-covid-19-vaccines). This is not an insignificant population of vulnerable people. - Mod.LK]

