[Data by country, area, or territory for 22 Apr 2022 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2022%20WHO%20Data%20Tables%20APR22_1650775892.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 8.3% of cases and 22.0% of deaths during the past 24 hours. It has reported more than 152.26 million cases, second to the European region as the most severely affected region. Brazil reported 36 750 cases in the last 24 hours. Canada, Puerto Rico, and Chile reported more than 1000 cases. Additionally, Panama, Barbados, Guatemala, and Peru reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases in the last 24 hours.

- The European region reported 51.2% of cases and 43.8% of deaths over the last 24 hours. It is the most affected region, with cumulative cases exceeding 212.38 million. Some countries reporting few or no cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Spain, Belgium (13 cases), Switzerland, Finland and Tajikistan, among others. A total of 22 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours: 1 country reporting more than 100 000 cases, 5 reporting more than 10 000, 16 reporting over 1000 cases, while 7 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 0.09% of daily case numbers and 2 deaths in the past 24 hours. It has reported a cumulative total of more than 21.68 million cases. Most countries did not report any cases over the last 24 hours. All reporting countries registered fewer than 200 cases over the last 24 hours.

- The African region reported 2.6% of daily cases and 3.8% of deaths during the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 8.71 million cases. South Africa (4406) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours followed by Zambia (344). Most of remaining countries reported below 50 in number of cases. A total of 37 countries did not report any cases over the last 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 34.1% of daily case numbers and 21.2% of deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 53.08 million cases. South Korea (81 058) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours followed by Australia, Japan, Vietnam, New Zealand, Malaysia, China, Singapore, and Lao PDR.

- The South East Asia region reported 3.5% of the daily newly reported cases and 8.8% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 57.68 million cases. Thailand (21 808) reported the highest number of cases followed by India (2451) and Bhutan (302).

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 22 Apr 2022, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

